        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–446: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-04">October 4,
                            1946</date>.]<lb/>[Received October 4—8:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1594. Following statement released to press by Embassy at 4 p.m., October 3:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The statement released by the Central News Agency in Nanking dated
                            September 30 to the effect that Generalissimo Chiang Kai Shek had agreed
                            to accept the proposal of General Marshall for a simultaneous meeting of
                            the Committee of Three and the Five Man Committee is incorrect in
                            attributing the proposal to General Marshall.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
